question: What is the official gene symbol of GCS1?
agent_answer:
The term "GCS1" is used as a gene symbol in different organisms. Here are some examples:

1. In Saccharomyces cerevisiae (baker's yeast), the official gene symbol is [GCS1](https://monarchinitiative.org/gene/SGD:S000002385).
2. In Drosophila melanogaster (fruit fly), the official gene symbol is also [GCS1](https://monarchinitiative.org/gene/FB:FBgn0030289).
3. In humans, the term "GCS1" is associated with two different genes: [ADAP1](https://monarchinitiative.org/gene/HGNC:16486) and [MOGS](https://monarchinitiative.org/gene/HGNC:24862).
4. In Schizosaccharomyces pombe (fission yeast), the official gene symbol is [gcs1](https://monarchinitiative.org/gene/PomBase:SPAC22F3.10c).
5. In Rattus norvegicus (rat), the official gene symbol is [Mogs](https://monarchinitiative.org/gene/RGD:69240).
6. In Mus musculus (mouse), the official gene symbol is also [Mogs](https://monarchinitiative.org/gene/MGI:1929872).

Please specify the organism if you are interested in a particular one.
